With an appeal to people to take oath to protect the ideals and thoughts of Swami Vivekananda, his birth anniversary was celebrated in different parts of the district on Tuesday.The district administration organised National Youth Day celebrations on the premises of the Government College for Women on Bengaluru-Mysuru highway here. Swamy, in-charge Assistant Director for the Department of Youth Empowerment and Sports, and others paid floral tributes.Speaking after the inauguration, Mr. Swamy urged the youth to work to eradicate poverty and illiteracy in the country. People, especially youngsters, should fight against corruption, he said. The thoughts of Swami Vivekananda are still relevant, lecturer K.P. Mrutyunjay said.The district administration organised the programme to spread awareness about the importance of Swami Vivekanandaâ€™s life and message among students.Principal V.T. Ramachandra, and NSS coordinator K.V. Narayan were present.Congress officeThe former Minister and Mandya District Congress Committee president M.S. Atmananda and others remembered the national youth icon at the MDCC office.The Congress leaders offered flowers to the portrait and urged people to follow the ideals of Swami Vivekananda.Jayanti celebrations were also held in different parts of the district.